ate the image file.  \n  \n## See Also  \n <xref:System.Windows.Media.DrawingContext>   \n [Imaging Overview](../../../../docs/framework/wpf/graphics-multimedia/imaging-overview.md)   \n [Drawing Objects Overview](../../../../docs/framework/wpf/graphics-multimedia/drawing-objects-overview.md)   \n [Using DrawingVisual Objects](../../../../docs/framework/wpf/graphics-multimedia/using-drawingvisual-objects.md)","nodes":[{"pos":[4,502],"nodes":[{"content":"How to: Encode a Visual to an Image File | Microsoft Docs","nodes":[{"pos":[0,57],"content":"How to: Encode a Visual to an Image File | Microsoft Docs","nodes":[{"content":"How to: Encode a Visual to an Image File | Microsoft Docs","pos":[0,57]}]}],"pos":[6,66],"yaml":true}],"content":"title: \"How to: Encode a Visual to an Image File | Microsoft Docs\"\nms.custom: \"\"\nms.date: \"03/30/2017\"\nms.prod: \".net-framework\"\nms.reviewer: \"\"\nms.suite: \"\"\nms.technology: \n  - \"dotnet-wpf\"\nms.tgt_pltfrm: \"\"\nms.topic: \"article\"\nhelpviewer_keywords: \n  - \"image files, encoding from visuals\"\n  - \"encoding image formats\"\n  - \"visuals, encoding to an image file\"\nms.assetid: 2036385b-ea47-4d54-8027-5797f52c8149\ncaps.latest.revision: 4\nauthor: dotnet-bot\nms.author: dotnetcontent\nmanager: \"wpickett\"","yamlblock":true},{"pos":[509,549],"content":"How to: Encode a Visual to an Image File","linkify":"How to: Encode a Visual to an Image File","nodes":[{"content":"How to: Encode a Visual to an Image File","pos":[0,40]}]},{"content":"This example demonstrates how to encode a <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Media.Visual&gt;</ph> object into an image file using a <ph id=\"ph2\">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Media.Imaging.RenderTargetBitmap&gt;</ph>and a <ph id=\"ph3\">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Media.Imaging.PngBitmapEncoder&gt;</ph>.","pos":[550,774],"source":"This example demonstrates how to encode a <xref:System.Windows.Media.Visual> object into an image file using a <xref:System.Windows.Media.Imaging.Ren